# Advanced MongoDB Query Operators & Aggregation

## 1. `$expr`

The `$expr` operator allows aggregation expressions to be used inside query filters.

### Purpose

Used when comparing:

* Field vs Field
* Field vs Calculation

### Example

```javascript
db.students.find({
   $expr:{
      $gt:["$marks","$passingMarks"]
   }
})
```

### Output

Returns students whose marks are greater than their passing marks.

### Another Example

```javascript
db.monthlyBudget.find({
   $expr:{
      $gt:[
         "$spent",
         {
            $divide:["$budget",2]
         }
      ]
   }
})
```

### Explanation

Finds all documents where:

```text
spent > budget / 2
```

### Common Operators Used with `$expr`

```javascript
$gt
$lt
$gte
$lte
$eq
$ne
```

### Interview Definition

`$expr` allows MongoDB queries to use aggregation expressions and compare fields within the same document.

