# 2. Aggregation Framework

Aggregation processes documents through multiple stages and returns computed results.

```text
Documents
   ↓
Stage 1
   ↓
Stage 2
   ↓
Result
```

---

## `$match`

Filters documents.

### Example

```javascript
db.students.aggregate([
{
   $match:{
      age:{ $gt:20 }
   }
}
])
```

### Purpose

Works similarly to `find()`.

---

## `$group`

Groups documents based on a field.

### Example

```javascript
db.sales.aggregate([
{
   $group:{
      _id:"$product"
   }
}
])
```

### Purpose

Groups all documents having the same product together.

---

## `$sum`

Calculates total values.

### Example

```javascript
db.sales.aggregate([
{
   $group:{
      _id:"$product",
      totalSales:{
         $sum:"$amount"
      }
   }
}
])
```

### Purpose

Calculates total sales per product.

---

## `$avg`

Calculates average values.

### Example

```javascript
db.students.aggregate([
{
   $group:{
      _id:null,
      averageMarks:{
         $avg:"$marks"
      }
   }
}
])
```

### Purpose

Returns average marks of all students.

---

## `$count`

Counts documents.

### Example

```javascript
db.students.aggregate([
{
   $count:"totalStudents"
}
])
```

### Output

```javascript
[
   {
      totalStudents:50
   }
]
```

---

## `$project`

Used to select, remove, rename, or create fields.

### Example

```javascript
db.students.aggregate([
{
   $project:{
      _id:0,
      name:1,
      marks:1
   }
}
])
```

### Purpose

Returns only selected fields.

---

## `$sort`

Sorts documents.

### Ascending Order

```javascript
db.students.aggregate([
{
   $sort:{
      marks:1
   }
}
])
```

### Descending Order

```javascript
db.students.aggregate([
{
   $sort:{
      marks:-1
   }
}
])
```

### Purpose

Orders documents by a field.

